    "title": "Incrementality Testing at Scale: Geo-Lift Experiments and Synthetic Control Methods",
    "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18860345",
    "publication_date": "2026-03-04",
    "description": "Attribution models answer 'who gets credit?' \u2014 incrementality testing answers 'would the sale have happened anyway?' This paper presents a comprehensive incrementality testing framework combining geo-lift randomized experiments with synthetic control methods (Difference-in-Differences, Synthetic Control Method, Bayesian Structural Time Series). The framework provides unbiased causal lift estimates with formal confidence intervals, enabling budget reallocation decisions grounded in experimental evidence. Provides ground-truth validation for Robinson (2026a) through (2026b).",
